Governor Samuel Ortom of PDP and his main challenger, Barrister Emmanuel Jime, has won at their various polling units in Guma and Makurdi LGAs respectively. Ortom scored 732 votes at Ako polling unit in LGEA primary school in Gbajimgba, headquarters of Guma while the APC candidate had zero votes. At the Ndabagi polling unit where Jime voted, the APC scored 159 leaving the PDP with a total of 19 votes. Ortom, PDP win in Benue govt house polling unit Massive victory for Atiku at Gov Ortom's unit PDP leads in Benue South